arts.ttl: Bromley brush aside Gillingham to extend unbeaten run and close on top seven
arts.sum: Louis Dennis, Jude Arthurs and Kamarl Grant struck for the visitors in a 3-0 win.

arts.ttl: “It was something for us to really fight for” - AFC Wimbledon boss says his side were driven by the chance to go second in League Two ahead of Gillingham win
arts.sum: A controversial decision in Wimbledons’ favour is something of a rarity this season, the side having seen a perfectly good 93rd-minute winner disallowed at Plough Lane just four days earlier against Swindon. The Dons finished 2024 with a victory at Plough Lane courtesy of a Matty Stevens (pictured) goal which appeared to go in off the in-form striker’s arm.
